        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 5:34PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 534 PM MDT, Trained spotters reported an area of strong
thunderstorms over Kirtland, or 10 miles west of Farmington, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Trained spotters reported quarter sized hail in Northeast
Farmington.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Farmington, Aztec, Shiprock, Kirtland, Upper Fruitland, Fruitland,
Ojo Amarillo, Nenahnezad, NAPI Headquarters and Flora Vista.

This includes Highway 64 between Mile Markers 23 and 59.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
